          The <strong>Bermuda Health Council (BHeC)</strong> is the statutory body responsible for
          regulating and planning Bermuda's health system. It publishes the official SHB rates,
          the approved insurer list, and the Health Insurance Act regulations.
        </p>
        <p style="margin-bottom: var(--space-4);">
          <a href="https://www.bhec.bm" rel="noopener" target="_blank" style="color: var(--color-sand);">bhec.bm</a>
          — the required starting point for any question about mandatory health coverage in Bermuda.
        </p>
        <p style="color: rgba(255,255,255,0.6); font-size: var(--text-sm); margin: 0;">
          Rates and coverage rules are updated annually. Always verify current figures at bhec.bm
          and confirm your employer's plan details in writing before you arrive.
        </p>
      </div>

    </div>
